      <p>A <a href="ch76s07.html#EpicMonsters(G-W)50">hoary hunter's</a> natural weapons are treated as epic for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.<a href="img/EpicMonsters(G-W).Hoary_Hunter.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/EpicMonsters(G-W).Hoary_Hunter.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id2355275"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="EpicMonsters(G-W)51"/>
        <p>A critical hit (or the blow that would kill or render a foe unconscious) from the <a href="ch76s07.html#EpicMonsters(G-W)50">hoary hunter's</a> blade does not wound the hunter's prey. Instead, the victim is bodily transported as per a <span class="emphasis"><em>soul <a href="ch43.html#SpellsA-B39">binding</a></em></span> spell heightened to 16th level (DC 30) into a diamond at the end of the sword's hilt.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2355323"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="EpicMonsters(G-W)52"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Spell-Like Abilities:</strong></span> At will-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E36">discern location</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch51.html#SpellsT-Z25">true strike</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch46.html#SpellsF-G25">fog cloud</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch47.html#SpellsH-L19">hold monster</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R17">plane shift</a></em></span>; 3/day-<span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E32">dimensional anchor</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E53">dominate monster</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch45.html#SpellsD-E45">greater dispel magic</a></em></span>; 1/day-mage's <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch48.html#SpellsM-O4">disjunction</a></em></span>,  <span class="emphasis"><em>contingent recall and <a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R74">resurrection</a>*</em></span>. Caster level 23rd; save DC 18 + spell level. <span class="emphasis"><em>*Contingent recall and <a href="ch49.html#SpellsP-R74">resurrection</a></em></span> is a variation on an epic spell. When slain, the <a href="ch76s07.html#EpicMonsters(G-W)50">hoary hunter</a> is actually transported, with its mount, back to the fey realm, where it is resurrected. The only way to truly slay the <a href="ch76s07.html#EpicMonsters(G-W)50">hoary hunter</a> is to defeat it in its home realm after this epic spell has been exhausted for the day.</p>
